.TH TRIM 1 "2026-03-09" "trim 1.0.0" "Bash String Trimming Utilities"
.SH NAME
trim, ltrim, rtrim, trimv, trimall, squeeze \- pure Bash string trimming utilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B trim
.RB [ \-e ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ string\  .\|.\|. ]
.br
.B ltrim
.RB [ \-e ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ string\  .\|.\|. ]
.br
.B rtrim
.RB [ \-e ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ string\  .\|.\|. ]
.br
.B trimv
.RB [ \-e ]
.RB [ "\-n \fIvarname\fR" ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ string\  .\|.\|. ]
.br
.B trimall
.RB [ \-e ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ string\  .\|.\|. ]
.br
.B squeeze
.RB [ \-e ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-V ]
.RB [ \-\- ]
.RI [ string\  .\|.\|. ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Six pure-Bash string trimming utilities that use native parameter expansion
with zero external dependencies.
Each utility works both as a standalone command and as a sourceable function.
.PP
When invoked with arguments, the string is processed and printed to stdout.
When invoked with no arguments, stdin is processed line by line.
.SS trim
Remove both leading and trailing blanks (spaces and tabs).
.SS ltrim
Remove leading blanks only.
.SS rtrim
Remove trailing blanks only.
.SS trimv
Trim leading and trailing blanks and optionally assign the result
directly to a named variable via
.BR \-n .
Must be
.B sourced
for variable assignment to work in the calling shell.
.SS trimall
Normalize whitespace: strip leading and trailing blanks, then collapse
all consecutive whitespace (spaces, tabs, newlines) to single spaces.
.SS squeeze
Collapse consecutive blanks (spaces and tabs) to single spaces while
.I preserving
leading and trailing whitespace.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-e
Process escape sequences
.RB ( \et ,
.BR \en ,
etc.\&) in the input string via
.BR printf\  %b .
.TP
.BI \-n\  varname
.RB ( trimv\  only)
Store the trimmed result in
.I varname
instead of printing to stdout.
Defaults to
.B TRIM
if
.I varname
is omitted.
Requires the utility to be sourced.
.TP
.B \-\-
End of options.
All subsequent arguments are treated as input strings.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.SH SOURCE MODE
Sourcing is the primary intended usage.
When sourced, each utility defines and exports its function without
executing any command-mode logic.
.PP
Source an individual utility:
.PP
.RS
.nf
\fBsource trim\fR
result=$(trim "\ \ hello\ \ ")
.fi
.RE
.PP
Source all utilities at once:
.PP
.RS
.nf
\fBsource /usr/local/share/yatti/trim/trim.inc.sh\fR
.fi
.RE
.PP
For
.BR trimv ,
sourcing is
.B required
when using
.B \-n
because subprocesses cannot modify parent shell variables.
.SH EXAMPLES
Command-line usage:
.PP
.RS
.nf
trim "\ \ hello world\ \ "         # "hello world"
ltrim "\ \ hello world\ \ "        # "hello world\ \ "
rtrim "\ \ hello world\ \ "        # "\ \ hello world"
trimall "\ \ multiple\ \ \ spaces\ \ "  # "multiple spaces"
squeeze "\ \ multiple\ \ \ spaces\ \ "  # "\ multiple spaces\ "
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pipeline usage:
.PP
.RS
.nf
cat file.txt | trim
grep pattern file.txt | trim | sort | uniq
.fi
.RE
.PP
Variable assignment with
.BR trimv :
.PP
.RS
.nf
source trimv
trimv \-n RESULT "\ \ hello world\ \ "
echo "$RESULT"   # "hello world"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Inline parameter expansion (avoids function call overhead):
.PP
.RS
.nf
v="${v#"${v%%[![:blank:]]*}"}"   # leading
v="${v%"${v##*[![:blank:]]}"}"   # trailing
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 22
Invalid option (EINVAL).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
These utilities use the POSIX
.B [:blank:]
character class, which matches space and tab only.
Unicode whitespace (U+00A0, U+2000\(enU+200A, etc.\&) is
.B not
trimmed.
This is intentional.
.PP
Requires
.B Bash 4.4+
for
.BR ${parameter@Q} ,
.BR inherit_errexit ,
and other features.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/trim
Installed commands (trim, ltrim, rtrim, trimv, trimall, squeeze).
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/yatti/trim/trim.inc.sh
Combined source file containing all function definitions.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
.BR sed (1),
.BR tr (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Open Technology Foundation
.br
.UR https://github.com/Open-Technology-Foundation/trim
.UE
